2.00	Howell-Jolly_body	Howell-Jolly body	This DNA appears as a basophilic (purple) spot on the otherwise eosinophilic (pink) erythrocyte on a standard H&amp;E stained blood smear. These inclusions are normally pitted out by the spleen during erythrocyte circulation, but will persist in individuals with functional hyposplenia or asplenia.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/Howell-Jolly_smear_2010-11-17.JPG/220px-Howell-Jolly_smear_2010-11-17.JPG
